Please answer the below core-java Questions:

What is programing language?
A. a programming language is a language that a program tell the computer what to do
What jdk contains or composed of and define each components?
A. JDK includes jdk and jre. JDK is the java development kit, while JRE is the java runtime environment.
JDK components are:
    1. Java compiler- compiles java lanaguage code into bytecode files
    2. java interpreter- is used to interpret the .java files which jave been compiled
    3. java disassembler- disassembly  tool that disassembles java files
    4. java header file generator- generates the c header and source files needed to implement methods and references object variables from source code.
    5. java documentation- documents Java source files, HTML pages defining the public/protected/nested classes, interfaces, constructors, methods, and fields
    6. java debugger- command line debugger for java, inspect and debugs java virtual machine
    7. java applet viewer- views java applets
What is IDE?
A. IDE is integrated development environment where you write code and compile programs. Has text editors/interpreters/compilers
